weka.gui.explorer
Interface ClustererPanelLaunchHandlerPlugin

public interface ClustererPanelLaunchHandlerPlugin

Interface to plugin that can take the current state of the Clusterer panel and execute it. E.g. A plugin could be made to train and evaluate the configured clusterer on remote machine(s).

For full access to the protected member variables in the ClustererPanel, an implementation will need to be packaged in weka.gui.explorer. The ClustererPanel looks for implementations when it is constructed, and will provide a new button (in the case of a single plugin) or a button that pops up a menu (in the case of multiple plugins) in order to invoke the launch() method on the plugin.
